 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Habitat suitability function</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Habitat suitability (HS) modeling uses information on a species dependency on the habitat to predict the likelihood of occurrence in a given area based on environmental variables (Franklin, 
  <a rid="ece33629-bib-0022" ref-type="ref" href="#ece33629-bib-0022">1995</a>; Hirzel &amp; Le Lay, 
  <a rid="ece33629-bib-0029" ref-type="ref" href="#ece33629-bib-0029">2008</a>; Pereira &amp; Itami, 
  <a rid="ece33629-bib-0049" ref-type="ref" href="#ece33629-bib-0049">1991</a>). It describes the quantitative relationship between the physical and biological factors in a given environment, and further the suitability of the given habitat for a specific species (Akçakaya &amp; Root, 
  <a rid="ece33629-bib-0003" ref-type="ref" href="#ece33629-bib-0003">2013</a>). We projected the model to the entire area of interest using Equation 2. As a logistic regression (
  <span class="italic">y</span>, Equation 3) was used to describe presence/absence of the Little Owl, the logit link function (Equation 2) describes the probability (
  <span class="italic">p</span>) that the owl is present (Akçakaya &amp; Root, 
  <a rid="ece33629-bib-0003" ref-type="ref" href="#ece33629-bib-0003">2013</a>):
  <div id="ece33629-disp-0002" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">(2)</span>
   <div id="nlm-math-2" class="math">
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mi">p</span>
     <span width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <span class="mn">1</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mo">exp</span>
       <div close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span class="mi">y</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
     <span width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mtext">where</span>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
